# Build System (BAI)

This document describes how BAI applies to this TypeScript monorepo project

## Overview

BAI orchestrates the lifecycle of this TypeScript monorepo by executing phases over units in dependency order. By default, BAI builds only packages in the dependency tree from selected apps; use `-all` to include all packages.

## Unit Types in This Project

- **NodeProject**: Root project unit - entry point for workspace discovery
- **NodeLib** (`typescript-lib`): TypeScript library packages - compile to JavaScript and generate types
- **FirebaseHosting** (`firebase-hosting`): Frontend applications - serve and deploy to Firebase Hosting
- **FirebaseFunction** (`firebase-function`): Backend applications - deploy as Firebase Functions

## Lifecycle Phases

- **Prepare**: Process `__package.json` templates → generate `package.json` files (replaces `?` with `workspace:*`, replaces `{{PARAM}}` with values)
- **Purge** (`-p`): Clean generated files (`package.json`, `pnpm-workspace.yaml`, `node_modules`, `dist`, etc.)
- **Install** (`-i` | `init`): Generate `pnpm-workspace.yaml` and run `pnpm i` across workspace
- **Lint** (`--lint`): Run linting on TypeScript packages
- **Compile** (always runs, `-nb` to skip): Compile TypeScript packages to JavaScript
- **Test** (`-t`): Run tests on packages (see [Running Tests](../tests/running-tests.mdc))
- **Launch** (`-l`): Launch applications (`-lbd` for backend debug mode)
- **Deploy** (`--deploy`): Deploy applications to Firebase

## Common BAI Commands

- `bai -h` - View all parameters
- `bai -up={pattern}` - Select packages by regex pattern
- `bai -t -tt=pure` - Run pure tests
- `bai -t -tt=firebase` - Run Firebase tests
- `bai -w` - Watch mode (build and watch for changes)
- `bai -se={env}` - Set environment (local, dev, staging, prod)